CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 24, 1962, pg. 35 reads: "Ace Comedian - The late Lehman Smith, Wylie Ave. favourite, gained fame as a comedian. He played to top spots in good old days and was rated tops as a dancer and singer.  In later years he became a powerful politician, doing his best chores in the Third Ward.  He was married to the late Helen Greenlee's sister. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Lehman Smith wearing suit wearing top hat, holding cane, and cigar in mouth, posed in front of building, another version
